level.heading: Waterfront property adjoining market lands; highways through or bounding market places.
level.text: ยง 20-575 Waterfront property adjoining market lands; highways through or bounding market places. Nothing contained in this chapter shall interfere with the jurisdiction of the department of ports and trade over any waterfront property in and around any market lands, nor with the jurisdiction of the commissioner of transportation over market lands, insofar as it concerns his or her powers over highways.
